But it's an irritation nonetheless.

00:45:10.339 --> 00:45:12.280
All right.

00:45:12.280 --> 00:45:19.290
Now I've hopefully explained to you the difference
between taste and smell and texture.

00:45:19.290 --> 00:45:22.890
Flavor is the combination of all three.

00:45:22.890 --> 00:45:24.630
It's the taste.

00:45:24.630 --> 00:45:30.840
Back to the chocolate example, the taste of
chocolate is bitter and sweet and maybe fruity

00:45:30.840 --> 00:45:35.829
depending on the chocolate varietal or how
it was prepared.

00:45:35.829 --> 00:45:42.800
The texture of chocolate is that melty, creamy,
hopefully not too waxy mouth feel.

00:45:42.800 --> 00:45:49.970
Then the aromas of chocolate are the lovely
browned, roasted, toasted, beany notes that

00:45:49.970 --> 00:45:50.970
we get.

00:45:50.970 --> 00:45:55.970
You might get some floral or some fruity notes
as well, depending on the varietal.

00:45:55.970 --> 00:45:58.750
That is the flavor of chocolate.

00:45:58.750 --> 00:46:02.470
When you talk about the flavor of butter,
you're talking about the combination of taste,

00:46:02.470 --> 00:46:05.819
texture, and aroma.

00:46:05.819 --> 00:46:08.819
Now we're going to talk about sight.

00:46:08.819 --> 00:46:14.630
We're going to talk about how we use our sense
of sight to experience food.

00:46:14.630 --> 00:46:15.869
Some of these things are pretty obvious.

00:46:15.869 --> 00:46:21.420
If I show you these two steaks, which one
is going to be more tender, the one on the

00:46:21.420 --> 00:46:22.890
top or bottom?

00:46:22.890 --> 00:46:24.790
Top, obviously.

00:46:24.790 --> 00:46:25.790
You knew that right away.

00:46:25.790 --> 00:46:28.880
You used your eyes to see that the marbling
